# GitHub Linguist overrides.
#
# The language bar should reflect the project's own software (the C++ protocol
# stack, the Python daemon, and the shared firmware Libraries), not the KiCad
# hardware designs or the per-board STM32 firmware projects. The latter are
# dominated by vendored ST CMSIS/HAL drivers and CubeMX-generated code (tens of
# megabytes of C), which otherwise make the repo read as ~99% C.
#
# Nothing below is deleted; these files stay in the repo and build normally.
# They are only excluded from the GitHub language statistics.

# All hardware (KiCad) is excluded.
hardware/** linguist-vendored

# All firmware is excluded EXCEPT the shared, hand-written Libraries.
firmware/** linguist-vendored
firmware/Libraries/** -linguist-vendored
# ...but External holds third-party libraries, so keep it excluded.
firmware/Libraries/External/** linguist-vendored
